@diegoperezguerrero9446It’s so weird. People seem to have allegiances to billionaires for some reason, but I can’t imagine being someone that deprives myself of something that I enjoy.

And it’s weird too, because it’s a blind loyalty to Vince. It’s not AEW’s style. It’s not the guys and girls who primarily had their rise in AEW because I’m sure these dudes are tripping all over themselves to cheer Penta, Ricky Saints, Ethan Page, etc. They’d lose their mind if MJF, Adam Page, etc showed up in WWE. It’s just some blind loyalty to a billionaire that doesn’t even know they exist.

But I enjoy both. And TNA. And other stuff. If you’re a -wrestling- fan, why would you want to limit your enjoyment? 🤷‍♂️
